cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of learning a quality function for super-resolution images using a deep neural network. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a neural network also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) could be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed system to microscopy images suggests that multimedia (cs.MM) could also be a possible sub-category.
